cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing the tractability of optimization problems for genetic algorithms and randomized search heuristics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper analyzes the complexities of two combinatorial problems, minimum spanning tree and single-source shortest paths. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimization algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper deals with complexity theoretic measures.
